-- ============================================================================
-- 008_college_seed_01.sql  —  part 1 of 11
-- Seed public.college (defined in 002_domain_entities.sql) from the UGC
-- "List of Colleges as on 31.07.2015" (public/list_of_college...pdf).
-- ownership_type maps the source "Govt / Non-Govt" column (Non-Government ->
-- PRIVATE, Government -> GOVERNMENT). place/district/pincode are best-effort
-- from free-form addresses; gaps are expected and can be backfilled later.
--
-- SPLIT INTO 11 FILES: the Supabase SQL Editor caps the size of a single
-- submission, so the full ~10k-row seed is split across 008_college_seed_01..11.
-- Run them IN ORDER. Each file is self-contained and idempotent — every INSERT
-- uses ON CONFLICT (name, place, pincode) DO NOTHING, so re-running any part (or
-- the same row appearing twice) is harmless. Same name in different towns = a
-- different college; identical (name, place, pincode) collapses to one.
-- (Alternative to the editor: run via psql / `supabase db push`, which has no
-- such size limit.)
-- ============================================================================

  on conflict (name, place, pincode) do nothing;
  on conflict (name, place, pincode) do nothing;
